    • GetXIntersectionPoints

      public java.util.List<double[]> GetXIntersectionPoints​(double xSteps, double lowerCap, double upperCap)
      Getter to return a list of positions in the coordinate system calculate with the formula and defined steps and boundaries.
      Parameters:
      xSteps - specifies the gap between each x-value on the x-axis.
      lowerCap - specifies the lower boundary of the value table and the start of the steps on the x-axis.
      upperCap - specifies the upper boundary of the value table which must not be a exact value.
      Returns:
      a list of double arrays with the exact coordinates of the points of the graph within the system of coordinates.
